1. This position will work together with the Electrician Supervisor to oversee the work, help to complete job on time and manage the workers at site.
2. Specific Resposibilities, Trainee to be involved in:

  Orientation of each project work scope
  Explain and demonstrate of safety requirement
  Explain and highlight the Risk management and Safety policy for each project.
  Generate reports on project schedule and work progress
  Attend site meeting and inspection with customers.
  Interpersonal skills with peers, customers, competitors, subcontractor and workers.

3. Competencies

  Work attitude, punctuality and responsibility at office and site
  Execute in planning vs actual work progress
  Meeting customer’s requirement in workmanship and quality
  Proper document submission and handover
  Managing people and work situation

4. Qualification required:&nbsp;

  ITE certificate

5. Eligibility Criteria for SGUnited Traineeships:&nbsp;

  Singapore Citizen or Permanent Resident and
  Graduated or graduating in calendar year 2019 or 2020 from ITEs, polytechnics, universities, or other educational institutions (e.g. private universities and overseas institutions); orb.
  Graduated earlier from above institutions and completed National Service in 2019 or 2020.
